This paper discusses machine learning techniques for modeling user needs and preferences, with a focus on selecting actionable attributes to maximize the probability of a desired outcome. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational engineering (cs.CE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the emphasis on supervised learning approaches and experimental validation in web analytics and e-learning domains, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
